Racktables Extensions v0.3.1
---------------------------------------------------------------
2013-08-28 - Mogilowski Sebastian <sebastian@mogilowski.net>
---------------------------------------------------------------
Website and HowTo: http://www.mogilowski.net/projects/racktables
---------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL:

General:

Move folder "extensions" into the racktables wwwroot folder.

"mv extensions /var/www/racktables" for example

---------------------------------------------------------------

On Racktables 0.19.13 or later:

Create or modify "local.php" in the "inc" folder.

"vim /var/www/racktables/inc/local.php"

Insert the following content:

<?php

# Load server report
require_once "extensions/reports/server-report.php";

# Load virtual machine report
require_once "extensions/reports/vm-report.php";

# Load switch report
require_once "extensions/reports/switch-report.php";

?>

or copy the example file.

---------------------------------------------------------------

On Racktables 0.20.0 or later:

Create or modify "extensions.php" in the "plugins" folder.

"vim /var/www/racktables/plugins/extensions.php"

Insert the following content:

<?php

# Load server report
require_once "../wwwroot/extensions/reports/server-report.php";

# Load virtual machine report
require_once "../wwwroot/extensions/reports/vm-report.php";

# Load switch report
require_once "../wwwroot/extensions/reports/switch-report.php";

?>

or copy the example file.

---------------------------------------------------------------

USAGE:

Login into racktables and go to "Reports".

Now you find "Server", "Virtual machines", "Switches" and "Custom" in the report menu.

Sort multiple columns simultaneously by holding down the shift key and clicking a second, third or even fourth column header! 

---------------------------------------------------------------
